<html><head></head><body dir=3D"auto" style=3D"overflow-wrap: =
break-word; -webkit-nbsp-mode: space; line-break: after-white-space;"><p =
dir=3D"auto" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">Good morning Grant,</p><p =
dir=3D"auto" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">Thank you so much for your =
email and for sharing the process document for my claim (C90306048) at =
23 Mays Street, Devonport. I really appreciate your effort to outline =
the framework and the chance to work together on this.</p><p dir=3D"auto" =
style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">I=E2=80=99ve looked over the process =
map and have a few thoughts to ensure we get this right, especially =
around safety and planning. I=E2=80=99ve heard from firefighters about =
significant fire damage and smoke exiting the roof=E2=80=94initially =
thought to originate there by Devonport Flagstaff=E2=80=94which has me =
concerned about the house=E2=80=99s condition. This makes me a bit =
uneasy about moving forward without some clarity.</p><p dir=3D"auto" =
style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">Could we please consider the following =
adjustments?</p><ul dir=3D"auto"><li><strong>Clarify Claim =
Scope</strong>: Is this process for both house and contents claims? If =
so, it would be helpful to link it to both policy numbers (P00004045285 =
for house, P00002855019 for contents) to ensure all coverage is =
included.</li><li><strong>Prioritize Health &amp; Safety</strong>: I=E2=80=
=99d feel more comfortable if we scheduled independent assessments =
(electrical, structural, gas, moisture/mould) before any major work, =
alongside the July 9 asbestos survey. The master electrician=E2=80=99s =
finding that the property is uninhabitable due to electrical hazards is =
a key concern.</li><li><strong>Assessment-Only Focus</strong>: Could we =
limit initial tasks to enabling damage assessment (e.g., securing the =
site, debris removal) rather than repairs (e.g., upstairs =
decontamination, curtain cleaning)? This would allow for a thorough =
evaluation and mutual agreement on remediation.</li><li><strong>Asbestos =
Survey Details</strong>: In orincipl, &nbsp; I=E2=80=99m happy to =
support the July 9 survey, but could you please share who will conduct =
it, the scope and tests involved, and how I can independently verify the =
results? Also, can the funding for this be covered under the claim =
preparation provision, as I=E2=80=99d like to ensure it=E2=80=99s done =
properly?</li><li><strong>Upstairs Cleaning Delay</strong>: The planned =
upstairs cleaning (July 21-25) feels premature for these reasons:<ol =
dir=3D"auto"><li>We need to assess damage before repair to preserve =
evidence.</li><li>If the gas unit (likely damaged) requires removal, the =
ceiling may need cutting, necessitating re-cleaning.</li><li>The =
electrician=E2=80=99s uninhabitable ruling requires electrical work =
first.</li><li>Firefighters switched off water (possibly gas?) and =
electricity, which must be assessed and remediated.</li><li>With 4 pets =
and hybrid work, noisy basement/deck/roof work makes living there =
untenable until completed.</li></ol></li><li><strong>Structural Engineer =
Guidelines</strong>: I previously asked about guidelines for paying a =
structural engineer. Could you please provide these, as I believe an =
independent assessment should precede any repair work?</li></ul><p =
dir=3D"auto" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">I=E2=80=99d love to =
discuss this with you and refine the timeline with firm dates for expert =
sign-offs and re-occupation only after safety is assured. Could you =
please share a revised plan by July 15, 2025? I=E2=80=99m really looking =
forward to working with you for a safe and fair outcome.</p><p =
dir=3D"auto" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">Kind regards,<br>
Raffaella del Prete</p><p dir=3D"auto" style=3D"white-space: =
pre-wrap;"><br></p><div class=3D"AppleOriginalContents" =
style=3D"direction: ltr;"><blockquote type=3D"cite"><div>On 7 Jul 2025, =
at 5:31=E2=80=AFPM, Grant Metson &lt;Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz&gt; =
wrote:</div><br class=3D"Apple-interchange-newline"><div><meta =
charset=3D"UTF-8"><div class=3D"WordSection1" style=3D"page: =
WordSection1; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Helvetica; =
font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; =
font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: start; =
text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; =
word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration: =
none;"><div style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, =
sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;">Good =
evening Rafaella,<o:p></o:p></span></div><div style=3D"margin: 0in; =
font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"><span =
style=3D"font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;">Thank you for taking the time =
to meet with me last week.<o:p></o:p></span></div><div style=3D"margin: =
0in; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"><span =
style=3D"font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;">As discussed, please find =
attached a process document which outlines the framework of how Tower =
Insurance will progress your claim.<o:p></o:p></span></div><div =
style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, =
sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;">This is a =
framework only and the process will change, as we move through each =
step, given that findings and results will affect the next step in the =
process. This will be a live document that will gather detail as we =
progress.<o:p></o:p></span></div><div style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: =
11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-family: =
Aptos, sans-serif;">However, I do trust that this will give you some =
insight and knowledge to allow us to participate in the process =
together.<o:p></o:p></span></div><div style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: =
11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-family: =
Aptos, sans-serif;">I look forward to speaking with you =
soon.<o:p></o:p></span></div><div style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: 11pt; =
font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-family: Aptos, =
sans-serif;">Please confirm back via email when you get a chance that =
you agree for Asset Restore to undertake the asbestos survey on the =
9<sup>th</sup><span class=3D"Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>=E2=80=93=
 as this is the first step in the process.<o:p></o:p></span></div><div =
style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, =
sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-family: Aptos, =
sans-serif;">Regards,<o:p></o:p></span></div><div style=3D"margin: 0in; =
font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"><span =
style=3D"font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;">Grant.<span =
class=3D"Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></span></div><div =
